This file marks that the project's wiki/ follows the six-section
documentation taxonomy (the crickets conventions `documentation` domain).
Four sections are always present; two are conditional:

  how-to/      — task-oriented recipes (onboarding walkthroughs live here,
                 numerically prefixed, carrying a `<!-- mode: tutorial -->`
                 hint so the gate holds them to tutorial discipline)
  reference/   — canonical lookup tables, flags, APIs
  designs/     — "Why we built X" design docs; load-bearing decisions are
                 recorded in each design's `## Amendment log` (the ADR model
                 is retired — there is no decisions/ section)
  explanation/ — narrative rationale, intent, trade-offs

  architecture/ — added only when a wiki/architecture.yml manifest declares it
  operational/  — added only when the repo's visibility is non-public

Presence of this marker enables strict-mode `check-wiki.py` for this
project. Do not remove unless you are migrating away from the taxonomy.

See:
- wiki/README.md — the convention as it applies here.
- https://github.com/alexherrero/crickets/wiki/crickets-conventions (the authoritative documentation convention)
